    <p>
      <!-- http://goose.berkeleybop.org -->
      <a href="[% base %]/goose" title="GO Online SQL
      Environment: query the GO database directly">GOOSE</a> is the GO
      Online SQL Environment. Using this, users may query the GO
      database directly using SQL, or edit one of the already made
      templates.
    </p>

    <p>
      <!-- http://gannet.berkeleybop.org -->
      <a href="[% base %]/gannet" title="Gannet: query the SOlr index
      directly">Gannet</a> is the Solr analog to GOOSE. A gannet is
      not a goose, but if it helps to remember, a kind if gannet is
      also known as the Solan (*cough* Solr) goose.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="[% base %]/amigo?mode=visualize&amp;session_id=[%
      session_id %]">Visualization</a>s of the GO graph. Freely make
      your own ontology graph, including label and color
      changes. Please see the documentation for
      more <a href="http://wiki.geneontology.org/index.php/AmiGO_Manual:_Visualize">details</a>.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      <a href="[% base %]/repl">REPL</a> is an
      interactive environment for working with BBOP JS against the GO
      data.
    </p>
    
